               <p>Our lodger 
               <persName id="t17820911-72-person794">
                  Charles
                   Stevens
               <interp inst="t17820911-72-person794" type="surname" value="Stevens"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17820911-72-person794" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17820911-72-person794" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was going to bed about eleven, he saw the prisoner and asked her what she had got in her lap, she said some things for Mrs. Smith; no such person lodged there; he brought her into the tap room and asked if I knew her, I said no, I never saw her, I asked him where he found her, he said on the two pair of stairs; I looked in her apron, and pulled out the things belonging to my girl who is thirteen; I went up stairs and found my drawers open; and found all my things gone out of them.</p>
               <p>(The things produced.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17820911-72-person795">
